100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On December 25, 1925, the world was abuzz with news of the ongoing negotiations in Geneva aimed at arms reduction, reflecting growing concerns over military expansions in Europe. Meanwhile, the United States continued its debate over Prohibition, with rising tensions and public discontent highlighting the challenges of enforcing the 18th Amendment. In the realm of science, the recent discovery of insulin's efficacy in treating diabetes garnered attention, promising new hope for patients.
